node.text: This book is so good, I had to share with everyone!! Forget Me Not is written in poetry form and is about a girl with Tourette syndrome who comes to embrace herself for who she is. There’s themes of friendship, acceptance, and more!  Trust me, you’ll love it!

node.text: My Grandma 할미 👵🏼 is a Korean immigrant, architect, and artist who came to the US, started her own company, and designs and builds housing for elderly residents. Today I visited her art gallery and thought about what an amazing example she is for me. I am so proud of her! She reminds me that I can achieve anything I set my mind to. I wuv you 할미!!!!
